      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The notion of pure meritocracy is a comforting but dangerous myth that conveniently ignores structural barriers. When starting lines are drastically different due to inherited wealth and racial bias, \"hard work\" operates within a fundamentally rigged game. True meritocracy cannot exist when access to quality education, capital, and social networks is determined by race, not individual effort. Wealth redistribution directly challenges this fallacy by leveling the playing field that the myth of meritocracy pretends to uphold.",
      "source": "target",
